cs.MA, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.SY 

The paper discusses the use of Multi-Agent Systems (MAS) and Service-Oriented Architectures (SOA) in digital ecosystems, which are both subfields of cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper also discusses distributed evolutionary computing, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The focus on developing robust and scalable self-organising architectures suggests a connection to cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the experimental simulations of the Digital Ecosystem architecture suggest a connection to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
